Morocco is one of Africa’s not-so-hidden gems. Yearly, the number of visitors to the North African country continues to rise as tourists from all over the world are drawn to its beauty and diversity. Morocco is every traveller’s dream. From its beautiful landscapes to its vibrant culture and its phenomenal architectural designs, Morocco is worthy of a place on your bucket list. Better yet, it is worthy to be your next travel destination. Here are five reasons why: <img class="aligncenter wp-image-726585 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Image-of-Morocco-culture-mint-tea.jpeg" alt="" width="1280" height="847" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Image-of-Morocco-culture-mint-tea.jpeg 1242w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Image-of-Morocco-culture-mint-tea-904x598.jpeg 904w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Image-of-Morocco-culture-mint-tea-487x322.jpeg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Image-of-Morocco-culture-mint-tea-974x645.jpeg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Image-of-Morocco-culture-mint-tea-320x212.jpeg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Image-of-Morocco-culture-mint-tea-640x424.jpeg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Image-of-Morocco-culture-mint-tea-600x397.jpeg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> The culture in Morocco is like nothing you will experience anywhere else in the world. You will see firsthand how the indigenes and locals live. Watch them make their handmade products, drink fresh mint tea you cannot find in your local grocery store, and experience the way of life of the Moroccans. If you’re looking for a unique cultural experience, Morocco is ideal. Read More: Adebayo Oke – Lawal Takes Paris Architectural Masterpiece in Marrakech If you have an eye for detail and design, Morocco will leave you spoilt for choice. Some of the most stunning designs and buildings found in the city of Marrakech will have you feeling like a kid in a candy store—ecstatic! Everywhere you turn, you will find elegance. Visiting the Sahara Desert is one of the main reasons people choose Morocco. If this is the only thing you do during your trip there, it will be well worth it. Riding a camel through the highest sand dunes is an experience of a lifetime you should not miss. In a local’s home where rugs are handmade If you plan to shop for the most traditional handmade and authentic goods such as rugs, spices, argan oil, leather goods, and so much more, Morocco is the place to be. Get your wallet ready as there is so much to buy in the local markets and medinas. The people of Morocco are friendly, approachable and hospitable. You will always feel welcome even as a guest. They will greet you with smiles, and if you are lucky, a cup of mint tea. Most of them speak English so interacting with them will not be a problem. Morocco has so much to offer to every traveller. When you book your flight, be sure to use our trusted travel agency – Travelstart